    "client_msg_id": "78946c01-fc26-4ad5-8f67-ba08b82d15b6",
    "text": "iPadOS \"math notes\" brings some spreadsheet/Calca mechanics to handwriting:\n<https://www.youtube.com/live/RXeOiIDNNek?si=D0I3FnVdzoCgV8em&amp;t=2790>\nOh, and they even added Bret Victor style variable \"scrubbing\".\n\n(Desktop also got builtin Math Notes, minus handwriting, briefly flashed 51:57 — looks very much like <http://Calca.io|Calca.io> / Soulver / NoteCalc etc.?)\n\nSo, are we \"Magic Ink\" yet?  (I'm not so much thinking of Bret Victor's essay as Ink&amp;Switch's experiments like <https://www.inkandswitch.com/inkbase/>, CrossCut &amp; Untangle ...)\nOn one hand nothing revolutionary, spreadsheets had much more power for decades.\nAnd yet a solid chunk of useful functionality is starting to move into taken-for-granted \"this is just how futuristic paper _naturally_ works\" territory :clap:.\nI expect long term it might make such \"what-if\" explorations accessible¹ to more people, and more importantly prepare people for more complex interactions on top?\n\n¹ well, once/IF it waters down to lower-end hardware.  Good-enough stylus tech remains expensive enough to be niche, _not_ evenly distributed :disappointed:",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1718300505.059309",
    "reply_count": 4,
    "reply_users_count": 3,
    "latest_reply": "1718352352.576129",
    "reply_users": [
      "U02QC0PPER3",
